# AWS Security Groups Fundamentals

## What Security Groups Are

Security Groups act as virtual firewalls for EC2 instances.

They control inbound and outbound traffic at the instance level.

## Why Security Groups Matter

They are essential for controlling network access and enforcing the principle of least privilege in AWS environments.

---

# Core Concepts

## Inbound Rules

- Control incoming traffic to an instance
- Define protocol, port range, and source

## Outbound Rules

- Control outgoing traffic from an instance
- Define protocol, port range, and destination

## Stateful Behavior

- If inbound traffic is allowed, the response is automatically allowed
- No need to configure separate return rules

## Default Behavior

- Deny all inbound traffic
- Allow all outbound traffic

